50|$|Re Brightlife Ltd 1987 1 Ch 200 is a UK {{insolvency}} law case, concerning {{the conversion of}} a floating charge into a fixed charge ("crystallisation"). It held that an automatic crystallisation clause {{was part of the}} parties’ freedom of contract. It could not be limited by court created <b>public</b> <b>policy</b> <b>exceptions.</b> The significance of the case was largely outpaced by the Insolvency Act 1986 section 251, which said a floating charge was one that was created as a floating charge.|$|R
